    <div class="instructions" data-platform="router">
     <div class="message center">
      <p class="collapsed-margins message-content">Your router’s configuration may vary. Consult your manual for more information.</p>
     </div>
     <ol>
      <li>Connect to your preferred wireless network.</li>
      <li>Enter your router’s gateway IP address in your browser.</li>
      <li>If prompted, fill in your username and password. This information may be labeled on the router.</li>
      <li>In your router’s configuration page, locate the <strong>DNS server</strong> settings.</li>
      <li>Write down any existing DNS server entries for future reference.</li>
      <li><span>Replace those addresses with the 1.1.1.1 DNS addresses:</span>
       <ul>
        <li>For IPv4: <strong class="code">1.1.1.1</strong> and <strong class="code">1.0.0.1</strong></li>
        <li>For IPv6: <strong class="code">2606:4700:4700::1111</strong> and <strong class="code">2606:4700:4700::1001</strong></li>
       </ul></li>
      <li>Save your settings, then restart your browser.</li>
      <li>You’re all set! Your device now has faster, more private DNS servers ✌️✌️</li>
     </ol>
    </div>
